data.content:
## What breaks: Sync I/O on Cosmos DB is **fully removed** in EF Core 11

In .NET 10, you could opt in to sync-over-async with the Cosmos provider. **In EF Core 11, that opt-in no longer exists.** Every synchronous call — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()` — will **always throw** at runtime. No configuration can restore the old behavior.

### Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This means callers must be updated to `await` these methods too — async propagates up the call chain.

**Additional Cosmos change to watch for:** empty owned collections now return an empty collection instead of `null`, so update any `is null` checks to `.Count == 0`.

Tracking issue: https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
